headline.main: CHINA SEES NO HELP IN MUSSOLINI'S FALL; Observers in Chungking Gloomy Over Pacific Prospects

lead_paragraph: CHUNGKING, China, Aug. 1 -- Although Benito Mussolini's meek departure from history was cordially applauded here it was not regarded as a blow to Japan.
abstract: Chungking observers gloomy over Allied prospects
